    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "The project aims at providing immediate protection to the monuments and sites affected by the 2015 earthquakes in Nepal, from further destruction or theft. Monuments still standing but at risk of collapse will be consolidated. By working with the Department of Archaeology, local communities, employing and training volunteers and building basic infrastructures, sites, monuments and relics will be protected from the looting and further destruction. The project will contribute to the restoration of local economies by creating professional training opportunities, employment. It also will be key to rehabilitating the tourism sector that is an important source of income for many communities."
      },
